    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 3.68,
      "end": 5.96,
      "text": "All LibraVax recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 7.06,
      "end": 11.72,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVax.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 12.48,
      "end": 18.14,
      "text": "Recorded by Annie Coleman in St. Louis, Missouri, in January 2006.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 20.1,
      "end": 21.12,
      "text": "Asop's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.72,
      "end": 24.6,
      "text": "The Stag and the Ox Stal.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.26,
      "end": 34.06,
      "text": "A Stag chased from his lair by the hounds, took refuge in a farmyard, and, entering a stable,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.64,
      "end": 40.24,
      "text": "where a number of oxen were stalled, thrust himself under a pile of hay in a vacant stall,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 40.88,
      "end": 44.7,
      "text": "where he lay concealed, all but the tips of his horns.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 45.92,
      "end": 51.58,
      "text": "Presently, one of the oxen said to him, What has induced you to come in here?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 52.22,
      "end": 56.08,
      "text": "Aren't you aware of the risk you are running of being captured by the herdsmen?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 56.98,
      "end": 60.72,
      "text": "To which he replied, Pray, let me stay for the present.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 61.44,
      "end": 65.3,
      "text": "When night comes I shall easily escape under cover of the dark.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 66.62,
      "end": 72.44,
      "text": "In the course of the afternoon, more than one of the farmhands came in, to attend to",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 72.44,
      "end": 77.88,
      "text": "the wands of the cattle, but not one of them noticed the presence of the Stag, who, accordingly,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 77.88,
      "end": 83.74,
      "text": "began to congratulate himself on his escape and to express his gratitude to the oxen.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 84.48,
      "end": 90.78,
      "text": "We wish you well, said the one who had spoken before, but you are not out of danger yet.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 91.42,
      "end": 97.38,
      "text": "If the master comes, you will certainly be found out, for nothing ever escapes his keen",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 97.38,
      "end": 97.96,
      "text": "eyes.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 99.36,
      "end": 105.5,
      "text": "Presently, sure enough, in he came and made a great to-do about the way the oxen were",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 105.5,
      "end": 105.76,
      "text": "kept.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-021",
      "start": 106.38,
      "end": 108.82,
      "text": "The beasts are starving, he cried.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-022",
      "start": 109.5,
      "end": 113.0,
      "text": "Here give them more hay, and put plenty of litter under them.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-023",
      "start": 113.78,
      "end": 121.14,
      "text": "As he spoke, he seized an armful himself from the pile where the Stag lay concealed, and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-024",
      "start": 121.14,
      "end": 122.52,
      "text": "at once detected him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-025",
      "start": 123.4,
      "end": 128.64,
      "text": "Calling his men, he had him seized at once, and killed for the table.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-026",
      "start": 130.92,
      "end": 133.46,
      "text": "End of the Stag in the Axe Stahl",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-027",
      "start": 135.76,
      "end": 135.9,
      "text": "End of the Stag in the Axe Stahl",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
